gomodel:SYNGO_1250  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Takamori et al show by subcellualr fractionation of a rat brain followed by proteomic analysis of CPG-purified SVs and immunoblotting of the fractions that tomosyn is enriched in SVs.. Experimental description: Purification of SVs from Rat Brain\nSVs were purified from rat brain, as described in detail in previous pub-\nlications (Nagy et al., 1976; Huttner et al., 1983) (see also Figure S1). To\nremove peripheral proteins from the SVs, the purified vesicle fraction\nwas resuspended with a 28-gauge needle in 0.1 M Na2CO3 (pH 11)\nand incubated on ice for 15 min. Immediately afterwards, the vesicles\nwere collected by centrifugation at 50,000 rpm for 20 min in a Beckman\nTi 100.2 rotor" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1250" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

